product_type2.name: Trench Coat
product_type2.description: Developed for Army officers in the pre-WWI era, a trench coat is practical and meant to withstand rough weather. The best one is the most classic beige and looks straight out of Film Noir, something that Alain Delon or Humphrey Bogart would wear. A style that looks like you’ve been wearing it for ages. Important rule—do not buckle your belt; just tie a knot in the front or back to look effortless.

product_type4.name: Low Top Sneakers
